# Architecture Patterns

## Domain-Driven Design
- Domain models in services/domain/models.py drive ALL decisions
- Database schema generated from SQLAlchemy models

## Repository Pattern
- ALL data access through services/repositories/
- Repositories return domain models, never database models
- No business logic in repositories

## CQRS Separation
- Read: services/queries/ (QueryRouter)
- Write: services/orchestration/ (workflows)
- Never mix read/write in same service

## Stateless Design
- Factories remain stateless
- Context passed as parameters
- No request data in instances

See docs/internal/architecture/current/architecture.md  for complete details.
